wfIRedundIfTable.name: wfIRedundIfTable
wfIRedundIfTable.description: WF_IREDUND_INTERFACE_TABLE - Interface REDUNDANCY This tabulates the interfaces within an interface redundancy group. All interfaces are indexed according to their physical slot and connector designation. All interfaces in the same circuit act as redundant (hot stand-by) interfaces for that circuit. At any given time, one hot stand-by interface is chosen to be the active interface for a circuit. The active interface is the only interface that is reading and writing data to/from the media.

wfIRedundIfDelete.name: wfIRedundIfDelete
wfIRedundIfDelete.description: Creation and deletion flag for this record. When set, it will cause this entry to be deleted from the MIB.

wfIRedundIfDisable.name: wfIRedundIfDisable
wfIRedundIfDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. A disabled interface will never be selected as the active interface for a circuit.

wfIRedundIfCct.name: wfIRedundIfCct
wfIRedundIfCct.description: The circuit number of the circuit to which the interface belongs. This interface will either act as the active interface for the the circuit or as a hot stand-by.

wfIRedundIfSlot.name: wfIRedundIfSlot
wfIRedundIfSlot.description: Slot ID of the interface, used as instance ID

wfIRedundIfPort.name: wfIRedundIfPort
wfIRedundIfPort.description: Port ID of the interface, used as instance ID

wfIRedundIfPrimary.name: wfIRedundIfPrimary
wfIRedundIfPrimary.description: Primary flag, indicates if this has been chosen as the primary interface. Only one interface in any circuit can be selected as a PRIMARY interface. The PRIMARY interface will have priority when an active interface is selected for a circuit. In general, if a PRIMARY circuit is available at active interface selection time, it will be chosen as the active interface.

wfIRedundIfActive.name: wfIRedundIfActive
wfIRedundIfActive.description: Active flag, indicates if this interface is the current active interface for the Interface Redundancy Group, or a standby interface, or not available to be used as active interface.

wfIRedundIfMACAddr.name: wfIRedundIfMACAddr
wfIRedundIfMACAddr.description: MAC Address being used by Interface Redundancy as Primary MAC Address.
